# This repo holds SCRIPTS + DOCS ONLY.
# It must never contain ROMs, BIOS/firmware, game disc images, or executables.
# The scripts stage game data under ~/emustaging (outside this repo) by default;
# the patterns below are a safety net against accidental commits.

# --- Disc images / ROMs ---
*.iso
*.bin
*.cue
*.chd
*.gdi
*.cdi
*.img
*.mdf
*.mds
*.ccd
*.sub
*.nrg
*.toc
*.pbp
*.cso

# --- Cartridge dumps ---
*.nes
*.sfc
*.smc
*.gb
*.gbc
*.gba
*.nds
*.n64
*.z64
*.v64
# NOTE: Mega Drive ROMs also use .md — but globbing "*.md" would swallow our
# Markdown docs (README.md, SETUP-GUIDE.md). Mega Drive dumps never live loose in
# this repo; they're covered by the roms/ and Emulation/ staging-dir ignores below.
*.gen
*.sms
*.gg
*.pce
*.32x

# --- Playlists that reference games ---
*.m3u

# --- BIOS / firmware ---
*.rom
bios/
BIOS/

# --- Executables / installers / libraries ---
*.exe
*.AppImage
*.dll
*.msi
*.bat

# --- Archives (commonly wrap ROMs) ---
*.7z
*.zip
*.rar
*.gz
*.tar

# --- Staging / scratch dirs ---
emustaging/
Emulation/
roms/
saves/

# --- personal config (keep out of the shareable repo) ---
# .env holds your real paths/IP; .env.example is the tracked template.
.env
.env.local
sync.env
scripts/sync.env
# SETUP-GUIDE.md is a personal, machine-specific worked run (real IP/paths) —
# kept local-only, not shipped. The generic guide is README.md + ON-DECK.md.
SETUP-GUIDE.md

# --- npm cruft (igir installs globally; a lone lockfile here is accidental) ---
package-lock.json
node_modules/

# --- OS junk ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
